Blogger Robert Alai is being sought by Central Police officers after he allegedly stormed the offices of Weekly Citizen and destroyed computers, scanner and printer belonging to the newspaper. The blogger is said to have arrived at the newspaper's offices at 12 pm on Tuesday. He was enraged by a story that the newspaper had written about him. One of the newspaper's editors Tom Alwaka accompanied by his lawyer Winston Ngaira reported the matter at the Central police station under OB number 84. A senior officer at Central police confirmed that Alwaka reported the case at the station.   